derivation.yuyuan_name: late Middle English: from Old French, or from Latin subsequent- 'following after' (from the verb subsequi)

entry.def: You use subsequent to describe something that happened or existed after the time or event that has just been referred to.

example.ex: ...the increase of population in subsequent years...
Those concerns were overshadowed by subsequent events.
example.tran: 随后发生的事使之前所关注的那些问题显得无足轻重。

entry.def: If something happened subsequent to something else, it happened after that thing.

example.ex: They won only one more game subsequent to their Cup semi-final win last year.
example.tran: 继去年在杯赛半决赛中获胜后，他们仅又赢过一场比赛。
